# Figma → React handoff

## When implementing from Figma

Always start by calling:

1. `get_design_context` (for the target frame/layer or current selection)
2. `get_variable_defs` (to extract tokens/styles used)
3. `get_screenshot` (only if layout/spacing is ambiguous)

Prefer existing components in the repo. Search in `src/components` first.

## React conventions

- Use functional components.
- Keep components small: split into subcomponents if >200 lines.
- Prefer composition over prop drilling.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, aria-label for icon-only buttons, keyboard nav.

## Styling conventions

- If project uses Tailwind: use Tailwind classes and existing utility patterns.
- If project uses CSS modules/styled-components: follow existing file naming and patterns.
- Do not invent new design tokens: use tokens from `get_variable_defs` or existing theme files.

## Assets

- If Figma layer has an Export setting, treat it as an asset:
  - vectors → SVG (preferred)
  - photos/bitmaps → PNG (2x if needed)
- Save assets under: `src/assets/` or `public/assets/` (repo's existing assets folder)
- Use deterministic names (kebab-case) derived from the layer name.
- Update any asset index exports if the repo has them.

## Code Connect (if available)

- If the design resembles an existing component, use Code Connect mapping:
  - check `get_code_connect_map`
  - add mapping when confident (node-id → component path)
